50|$|<b>Bonnethead</b> {{sharks are}} the only sharks known to exhibit sexual {{dimorphism}} in the morphology of the head. Adult female <b>bonnethead</b> sharks have a broadly rounded head, whereas males possess a distinct bulge along the anterior margin of the cephalofoil. This bulge is formed by the elongation of the rostral cartilages of the males {{at the onset of}} sexual maturity and corresponds temporally with the elongation of the clasper cartilages.|$|E
